    <title ixia_locid="1">[RC:steps] Assigning a new host node</title>
    <shortdesc ixia_locid="2">You can use <nameliteral ixia_locid="3">controller-0</nameliteral> to
        assign a configuration or <term ixia_locid="4">personality</term> (controller, compute, or
        storage, for example) to a new node.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author ixia_locid="5">Jim Owens</author>
    </prolog>
    <rcbody>
        <context id="context_N10027_N10024_N10001" ixia_locid="6">
            <p ixia_locid="7">You can assign one of the following personalities.</p>
            <simpletable id="simpletable_ysx_xr5_k4">
                <strow>
                    <stentry ixia_locid="8">
                        <p ixia_locid="9">controller</p>
                    </stentry>
                    <stentry ixia_locid="10">
                        <p ixia_locid="11">redundant controller for failover</p>
                    </stentry>
                </strow>
                <strow>
                    <stentry ixia_locid="12">
                        <p ixia_locid="13">compute</p>
                    </stentry>
                    <stentry ixia_locid="14">
                        <p ixia_locid="15">processing node</p>
                    </stentry>
                </strow>
                <strow product="tis_nonregion">
                    <stentry ixia_locid="16">
                        <p ixia_locid="17">storage</p>
                    </stentry>
                    <stentry ixia_locid="18">
                        <p ixia_locid="19">data storage node </p>
                    </stentry>
                </strow>
            </simpletable>
        </context>
        <prereq id="prerequisites" ixia_locid="20">
            <p ixia_locid="111">Before initializing a node, ensure that the following conditions are
                satisfied:</p>
            <ul id="ul_adx_kts_v4">
                <li ixia_locid="112">
                    <p id="prereq-hw-requirements" ixia_locid="21">The node must meet the hardware
                        requirements for the personality to be assigned.<ph ixia_locid="354" product="tis_region"> For more information, see <cite ixia_locid="144">Titanium Server Installation: Hardware
                        Requirements</cite></ph>.</p>
                    <note id="note_N100A7_N10093_N1008F_N10085_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="823" type="caution">
                        <p ixia_locid="824"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="825">CGTS-4159 added caution re SW RAID</draft-comment>Software RAID is
                            not supported.</p>
                    </note>
                </li>
                <li ixia_locid="113">
                    <p id="prereq-controller-0-ready" ixia_locid="23">Controller-0 must be installed
                        and configured.</p>
                </li>
                <li ixia_locid="136" product="tis_nonregion">
                    <p id="prereq-computing-node-PXE-connected" ixia_locid="138">The node must be
                        connected to the internal management network or PXE boot network using an
                        Ethernet interface configured for PXE boot.</p>
                </li>
                <li ixia_locid="137" product="tis_region">
                    <p ixia_locid="139">The node must be connected to the internal management network
                        using the PXE boot network.</p>
                </li>
                <li ixia_locid="140" product="tis_nonregion">
                    <p ixia_locid="355">The node must be configured in the BIOS to boot from the
                        internal management network or PXE boot network.</p>
                </li>
                <li ixia_locid="141" product="tis_region">
                    <p ixia_locid="143">The node must be configured in the BIOS to boot from the PXE
                        boot network.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </prereq>
        <steps id="steps_N100AB_N10029_N10001">
            <step id="step_N1007C_N10079_N1002E_N10001" ixia_locid="232">
                <!-- For a host-add installation (Regions), the first step (1 of 3).-->
                <!-- For a host-update installation (CLI), not used. -->
                <!-- For a Horizon installation, not used. -->
                <cmd ixia_locid="233">Add the host to the system inventory.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="234">
                    <note id="note_N10086_N10083_N1007C_N10079_N1002E_N10001" ixia_locid="235">
                        <p ixia_locid="236">The host must be added to the system inventory before it
                            is powered on.</p>
                    </note>
                    <p ixia_locid="237">On <nameliteral ixia_locid="238">controller-0</nameliteral>,
                        acquire Keystone administrative privileges:</p>
                    <codeblock ixia_locid="239"><systemoutput ixia_locid="240">$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="241">source /etc/nova/openrc</userinput></codeblock>
                    <p ixia_locid="242"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="538">US62814,
                            US62816 update host-add parameters</draft-comment><draft-comment author="rstone" ixia_locid="745">US63466 adds -D; CGTS-4254 clarify when
                            hostname is used</draft-comment>Use the <cmdname ixia_locid="621">system
                            host-add</cmdname> command to add a host and specify its personality.
                        You can also specify the device used to display messages during boot.</p>
                    <note id="note_N10146_N10109_N100F9_N100F5_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="826">
                        <p ixia_locid="827">The <parmname ixia_locid="828">hostname</parmname>
                            parameter is required for compute hosts. For controller and storage
                            hosts, it is ignored.</p>
                    </note>
                    <codeblock ixia_locid="356"><systemoutput ixia_locid="357">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="358">system host-add  -p <varname ixia_locid="359">personality</varname> -n <varname ixia_locid="246">hostname</varname> \
[-l <varname ixia_locid="666">location</varname>] [-o <varname ixia_locid="361">install_output</varname>[-c <varname ixia_locid="360">console</varname>]] [-b <varname ixia_locid="735">boot_device</varname>] \
[-r <varname ixia_locid="736">rootfs_device</varname>] [-m <varname ixia_locid="248">mgmt_mac</varname>] [-i <varname ixia_locid="362">mgmt_ip</varname>] [-D <varname ixia_locid="746">ttys_dcd</varname>] \
[-T <varname ixia_locid="309">bm_type</varname> -M <varname ixia_locid="310">bm_mac</varname> -I <varname ixia_locid="311">bm_ip</varname> -U <varname ixia_locid="312">bm_username</varname> -P <varname ixia_locid="313">bm_password</varname>]</userinput>
</codeblock>
                    <p ixia_locid="363">where</p>
                    <parml id="host-add_parms">
                        <plentry ixia_locid="364">
                            <pt ixia_locid="365"><varname ixia_locid="366">hostname</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="367">
                                <p ixia_locid="368">is a name to assign to the host (used for
                                    compute nodes only)</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="639">
                            <pt ixia_locid="640"><varname ixia_locid="641">personality</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="642">
                                <p ixia_locid="643" product="tis_region">is the host type (<option ixia_locid="644">controller</option> or <option ixia_locid="645">compute</option>)</p>
                                <p ixia_locid="646" product="tis_nonregion">is the host type <ph ixia_locid="647">(<option ixia_locid="648">controller</option>, <option ixia_locid="649">storage</option>, or <option ixia_locid="650">compute</option>)</ph></p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="667">
                            <pt ixia_locid="668"><varname ixia_locid="669">location</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="670">
                                <p ixia_locid="671">is a string describing the location of the host</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="376">
                            <pt ixia_locid="377"><varname ixia_locid="378">console</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="379">
                                <p ixia_locid="380">is the output device to use for message display
                                    on the host (for example, <option ixia_locid="381">tty0</option>). The default is <option ixia_locid="382">ttys0,
                                        115200</option>.</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="383">
                            <pt ixia_locid="384"><varname ixia_locid="385">install_output</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="386">
                                <p ixia_locid="387">is the format for console output on the host
                                        (<option ixia_locid="388">text</option> or <option ixia_locid="389">graphical</option>). The default is <option ixia_locid="390">text</option>.</p>
                                <note id="note_N108C1_N108A9_N1089D_N10858_N107F0_N107DF_N100F5_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="1041">
                                    <p ixia_locid="1042"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="1043">CGTS-5076 graphical installation
                                            disabled</draft-comment>The <option ixia_locid="1044">graphical</option> option currently has no effect.
                                        Text-based installation is used regardless of this
                                        setting.</p>
                                </note>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="508">
                            <pt ixia_locid="509"><varname ixia_locid="510">boot_device</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="511">
                                <p ixia_locid="512">is the host device for boot partition, relative
                                    to <filepath ixia_locid="513">/dev</filepath>. The default is
                                        <option ixia_locid="514">sda</option>.</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="515">
                            <pt ixia_locid="516"><varname ixia_locid="517">rootfs_device</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="518">
                                <p ixia_locid="519">is the host device for rootfs partition,
                                    relative to<filepath ixia_locid="520"> /dev</filepath>. The
                                    default is <option ixia_locid="521">sda</option>.</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="405">
                            <pt ixia_locid="406"><varname ixia_locid="407">mgmt_mac</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="408">
                                <p ixia_locid="409">is the MAC address of the port connected to the
                                    internal management or PXE boot network.</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="410">
                            <pt ixia_locid="411"><varname ixia_locid="412">mgmt_ip</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="413">
                                <p ixia_locid="414">is the IP address of the port connected to the
                                    internal management or PXE boot network, if static IP address
                                    allocation is used.<note id="note_N1029B_N10297_N10293_N10287_N1017A_N100F6_N100E6_N100E2_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="681" product="tis_region">
                                        <p ixia_locid="682"> The <varname ixia_locid="734">mgmt_ip</varname> option is not used for a
                                            controller node.</p>
                                    </note></p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="809">
                            <pt ixia_locid="810"><varname ixia_locid="811">ttys_dcd</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="812">
                                <p ixia_locid="813">is set to <nameliteral ixia_locid="814">True</nameliteral> to
                                    have any active console session automatically logged out when
                                    the serial console cable is disconnected, or
                                        <nameliteral ixia_locid="815">False</nameliteral> to disable this behavior.
                                    The server must support data carrier detect on the serial
                                    console port.</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="315">
                            <pt ixia_locid="321"><varname ixia_locid="327">bm_type</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="333">
                                <draft-comment author="rstone" ixia_locid="743">US64066 adds Quanta</draft-comment>
                                <p ixia_locid="339">is the board management controller type (<option ixia_locid="348">iLO3</option>, <option ixia_locid="353">iOL4</option> or <option ixia_locid="744">Quanta</option>)</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="316">
                            <pt ixia_locid="322"><varname ixia_locid="328">bm_mac</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="334">
                                <p ixia_locid="340">is the board management controller MAC
                                    address</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="317">
                            <pt ixia_locid="323"><varname ixia_locid="329">bm_ip</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="335">
                                <p ixia_locid="341">is the board management controller IP
                                    address</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="318">
                            <pt ixia_locid="324"><varname ixia_locid="330">bm_username</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="336">
                                <p ixia_locid="342">is the username for board management controller
                                    access</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                        <plentry ixia_locid="415">
                            <pt ixia_locid="416"><varname ixia_locid="417">bm_password</varname></pt>
                            <pd ixia_locid="418">
                                <p ixia_locid="419">is the password for board management controller
                                    access</p>
                            </pd>
                        </plentry>
                    </parml>
                </info>
                <stepxmp ixia_locid="279">
                    <p ixia_locid="280">For example:</p>
                    <codeblock ixia_locid="251"><systemoutput ixia_locid="253">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="255">system host-add -n compute-0 -p compute -m 08:00:27:5C:97:DB</userinput>
<systemoutput ixia_locid="801">+---------------------+--------------------------------------+
| Property            | Value                                |
+---------------------+--------------------------------------+
| action              | none                                 |
| administrative      | locked                               |
| availability        | offline                              |
| bm_ip               | None                                 |
| bm_mac              | None                                 |
